# Values — {{ORG_NAME}}

_What {{OWNER_NAME}} won't trade off, even under pressure. Agents
read these to know which judgment calls are calls (open) and which
aren't (closed)._

_Derived from interview {{INTERVIEW_DATE}}. Edit freely._

---

## What I value

{{CORE_VALUES}}

_(5-7 values, each a short phrase. These are the things
{{OWNER_NAME}} would refuse to trade away even for big wins.)_

## What good work looks like

{{WORK_QUALITY_STANDARDS}}

_(The qualities {{OWNER_NAME}} recognizes as excellent work — in
their own work and in others'. Used by agents to calibrate their
own output.)_

## Relationships I prioritize

{{KEY_RELATIONSHIPS}}

_(Categories of people whose call always comes first. Family, key
clients, longtime collaborators, etc. — by category, not by
specific person.)_

## How I treat people

{{INTERPERSONAL_PRINCIPLES}}

_(Default communication style, when to escalate, what kinds of
asks are reasonable, how to handle disagreement. Agents speaking
on {{OWNER_NAME}}'s behalf calibrate against these.)_

## What I refuse to do

{{NON_NEGOTIABLES}}

_(Explicit anti-list. Things {{OWNER_NAME}} won't engage with no
matter how attractive the upside. Agents enforce these as hard
ceilings — they don't get overridden by autonomy level.)_

## How I want to be challenged

{{CHALLENGE_PREFERENCES}}

_({{OWNER_NAME}} learns by being challenged. This documents how —
adversarial review, specific failure modes, evidence first, etc.
Agents (especially Analyst) calibrate critique against this.)_

---

_When a value is being tested by a decision, the answer here
matters more than the goal being pursued. Goals describe what
we're aiming for; values describe how we refuse to aim there._
